<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6193&amp;p=58610#p58610"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NOP taking many addressing modes, is that so?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6193&amp;p=58610#p58610"><![CDATA[
Puzznic has a two-byte nop.  If you don't emulate it as a two byte nop (for instance, you treat all illegal instructions as a one byte nop), then the second byte is a BRK instruction, and that messes things up.<br /><br />Is Puzznic a bad dump?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Mar 18, 2010 10:31 pm</p><hr />
